<p>One of the major features that sets Bitwig 2 apart from other DAWs (such as <a href="https://www.ableton.com">Ableton Live</a>) is Note Expression.</p>

<p>Note Expression, at its core, allows you to apply modulation of certain parameters to specific notes. The original midi spec only allows for control messages to be attached to the whole stream of data. With Note Expression, you can have a complex part where only certain notes that are specifically controlled.</p>

<p>After the break Iâ€™ll break it down even further with some examples.</p>

